      <description>&lt;p&gt;Gotra system of Śūdras as per Śeṣakṛṣṇa&amp;rsquo;s Śūdrācāraśiromaṇi -&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Using the name, of some popular person born in a good lineage, as the Gotra.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;In case of being born from a duly wedded Dvija father &amp;amp; a Śūdra mother, using the Gotra of the father.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Using the Gotra of the Upadeśaka (instructor) Brāhmaṇa as one&amp;rsquo;s Gotra.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol start=&#34;4&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Using &amp;lsquo;Kāśyapa&amp;rsquo; as the Gotra.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
